Title: Object: Joseph gouverneur d'Egypte
Description: Plate 9: Joseph governs over Egypt; he stands on a platform at centre, surrounded by guards, and observes as below some figures can be seen carrying large sacks of grain; after a drawing formerly attributed to Rembrandt; lettered state Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Anne Claude Philippe de Tubières, Comte de Caylus
Curator's comments: Plate 9 from a series of ten, see 1865,0208.1 for comment.
Bibliographic references: IFF / Inventaire du Fonds Français: Bibliothèque Nationale, Département des Estampes (378(9).II)
Acquisition notes: The Caylus set was purchased for the BM at an unidentified sale at Sotheby's for 8s
